{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01KTCzWo9oZccpx1hN3PhGFc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The CLI returned `blocked: true` with `blocking_reasons: [\"failed_required_artifact\"]`. According to the spec-inject instructions, when `blocking_reasons=[\"failed_required_artifact\"]`, I should:\n- Present the CLI's `recommended_next_action` (`\"run /spec-core or /spec-core --all before /spec-inject\"`) and the `warnings` details\n- Suggest running `/spec-core --all`\n\nThe warnings indicate:\n1. \"Source Retrieval Index update failed\"\n2. \"Related Sections retrieval backend failure: [Errno 111] Connection refused; canonical related_sections artifact is not updated. Restore Qdrant connectivity and run /spec-core --rebuild.\"\n\n\nI shouldn't automatically execute `/spec-core` — I need to present these findings to the user and let them decide how to proceed.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1116,"cache_read_input_tokens":25539,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1116},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bff4d1d0-ef8c-444b-b5c3-23f9f0dda6c0","uuid":"e50344d6-ce87-4e01-9dce-ca8100825e97","request_id":"req_011CbJa9KAX2gk1fd751tawY"}
